[Aseptic meningitis is a common manifestation of enterovirus infection. In
this outbreak Echovirus type 17 has been implicated. Echoviruses types
11-27 are now ranked as a single group (species) of closely related
enteroviruses. Although non-paralytic poliovirus infection often manifests
itself as aseptic meningitis, the use of poliovirus vaccine to control an
outbreak of aseptic meningitis is an unusual procedure of dubious worth
since there is no serological relationship between Echovirus 17 and
Poliovirus. - Mod.CP
